    <briefdescription>
<para>Slot connection is the connection information held by a connection tracker. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A slot can have zero to many connection objects, depending on how many signals it is connected to.</para>
<para>A connection contains:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ref refid="classDali_1_1Callback" kindref="compound">Callback</ref> (slot)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="classDali_1_1SlotObserver" kindref="compound">SlotObserver</ref> -interface provided by the signal</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>It holds a pointer to the callback, but does not own it. @SINCE_1_0.0 </para>
    </detaileddescription>
